# Required: Anthropic API key for the extraction pipeline.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Optional: override the Claude model used for extraction.
# Defaults to claude-sonnet-4-6 if unset. claude-opus-4-7 is more accurate
# but ~5x costlier; claude-haiku-4-5 is faster and cheaper for simple invoices.
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Optional: canonical origin used by metadata, robots, sitemap, and
# JSON-LD. Falls back to VERCEL_PROJECT_PRODUCTION_URL, then localhost.
SITE_URL=https://invoiceflow.example.com

# Optional: aggregate monthly cost ceiling in USD. The /api/extract route
# rejects new requests with HTTP 429 and code: "monthly-budget-exhausted"
# when the calendar-month cumulative Anthropic cost reaches this value.
# Defaults to 25 if unset. Resets on the 1st of each calendar month (UTC).
# Per-Fluid-Compute-instance, under horizontal scale, effective ceiling
# is roughly instance_count × MONTHLY_BUDGET_USD. Documented trade-off
# matching the per-instance rate limiter and rolling-median cost cap.
# Note: a value of 0, an empty string, or any non-numeric input falls
# through to the default 25 (fail-safe; prevents a malformed env var
# from producing a zero-budget DoS-of-self). To raise the ceiling for
# launch-week traffic, set a larger number (e.g., 50). To "disable"
# for testing, set a deliberately large value (e.g., 9999).
MONTHLY_BUDGET_USD=25

# Optional: override the Tellsight no-account demo URL exposed by the
# CSV-success CTA and the monthly-budget-exhausted error CTA. Must be
# an HTTPS URL or the placeholder guard suppresses the link entirely
# (see src/lib/site.ts#isTellsightDemoUrlConfigured). NEXT_PUBLIC_
# prefix is required because the value is consumed in Client Components
# and must be inlined into the client bundle. Defaults to a placeholder
# (https://tellsight.example.com/demo) which suppresses the CTA link.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TELLSIGHT_DEMO_URL=https://tellsight.coreystevens.dev/demo
